# CVE-2021-23358 — underscore < 1.12.1, Prototype Pollution
# Location: /var/ossec/framework/node_modules/underscore/ (Wazuh Agent 4.9.2 embedded Node.js)
# Risk assessment:
#   - Wazuh uses this internally for its Python framework tooling; not exposed to external input.
#   - The vulnerable template() function is not called with untrusted data in this context.
#   - Updating underscore inside Wazuh's internal node_modules risks breaking Wazuh internals.
#   - Mitigated by: Wazuh runs isolated inside the gateway container with no direct external exposure.
# Accepted risk: LOW  |  Next review: Wazuh Agent >= 5.0.0 or CVE severity upgrade
CVE-2021-23358
